# Grok Build Environment Configuration
#
# DigitalOcean Gradient serverless inference (recommended):
#   GRADIENT_KEY     Gradient model access key (Gradient > API Keys >
#                    Model Access Keys in the DigitalOcean control panel)
#   GRADIENT_MODEL   Default model alias from /root/.grok/config.toml, e.g.
#                    gpt-5-5 (default), gpt-5-3-codex, claude-opus-4-8,
#                    deepseek-v4-pro, kimi-k2-6, qwen3-coder-flash
#   GRADIENT_ROUTER  Optional. Name of a DigitalOcean Intelligent Inference
#                    Router attached to GRADIENT_KEY (in the control panel). If
#                    set, requests route through "router:<name>" using the SAME
#                    key and the router becomes the default model.
#
# xAI account (alternative): leave GRADIENT_KEY empty and either run
#   `grok login --device-auth` on the droplet, or set an xAI API key:
#   XAI_API_KEY      xAI API key (xai-...) from https://console.x.ai
#
# On first boot, 001_onboot reads /etc/environment first, then this file.
# If GRADIENT_KEY (or XAI_API_KEY) is set in either place, Grok Build is
# configured automatically and the interactive setup wizard is skipped.
# Otherwise run the wizard on first SSH login: /opt/setup-grok-build.sh

GRADIENT_KEY=
GRADIENT_MODEL=gpt-5-5
GRADIENT_ROUTER=
XAI_API_KEY=
